dcterms:description: The MIES dataset consists of the target variable IE, i.e. the self-identification as introvert or extrovert, and 95 features, thereof 91 items measuring the degree of extraversion on a 5-point Likert scale, 3 demographic items, and 1 item indicating the date of survey submittal.
dcterms:title: Multidimensional Introversion-Extraversion Scales (MIES)

dcterms:creator: K. W. P. Chawla
N. V. Bowyer
K. W. Hall
dcterms:description: SMOTE is a technique that synthesizes new class instances of the minority class by interpolation with k-nearest neighbors to reduce bias during training.
dcterms:title: SMOTE Dataset

dcterms:creator: H. He
Y. Bai
E. A. Garcia
S. Li
dcterms:description: ADASYN is a method that corrects the minority class by oversampling and adaptively gives higher weights for the misclassified samples.
dcterms:title: ADASYN Dataset
